WEBVTT

00:00:00.350 --> 00:00:06.374
As a house administrator, you may also be a resident. My

00:00:06.374 --> 00:00:12.398
Laundry Plan contains your private apartment bookings. Administration is where you

00:00:12.398 --> 00:00:18.421
handle tasks for the house. Each administrative action is attributed to

00:00:18.421 --> 00:00:23.350
your personal identity, not to the shared apartment account.

00:00:24.350 --> 00:00:30.968
The administration overview places important tasks before general figures.

00:00:30.968 --> 00:00:37.585
First review urgent incidents, blocked equipment and pending functional

00:00:37.585 --> 00:00:44.203
checks. Invitations, account notices, recurring appointments and general information

00:00:44.203 --> 00:00:49.350
for your house follow after those tasks.

00:00:50.350 --> 00:00:57.100
For a new resident, first define the stable apartment label and

00:00:57.100 --> 00:01:03.850
the name shown on the doorbell. Add the resident email address

00:01:03.850 --> 00:01:10.600
and send a time-limited invitation. The personal sign-in is created only

00:01:10.600 --> 00:01:17.350
when the invitation is accepted, with the correct apartment already assigned.

00:01:18.350 --> 00:01:25.497
Account administration shows active, invited and blocked people. Before

00:01:25.497 --> 00:01:32.644
helping with recovery, verify the identity, email address and

00:01:32.644 --> 00:01:39.791
apartment assignment. Never replace another person's email address merely

00:01:39.791 --> 00:01:45.350
to receive their password reset link yourself.

00:01:46.350 --> 00:01:52.898
House and Equipment is where you manage washing machines, tumblers and

00:01:52.898 --> 00:01:59.445
drying rooms for your house. Use clear names so the calendar,

00:01:59.445 --> 00:02:05.993
issue report and logbook refer to the same resource. A deactivated

00:02:05.993 --> 00:02:11.350
or blocked resource must no longer appear as bookable.

00:02:12.350 --> 00:02:19.647
The machine and room logbook preserves reports, decisions and work

00:02:19.647 --> 00:02:26.945
performed. Record observations and measures factually with the date and

00:02:26.945 --> 00:02:34.242
affected resource. Existing entries are not deleted; they are extended

00:02:34.242 --> 00:02:39.350
or completed by the next workflow step.

00:02:40.350 --> 00:02:48.188
Review a resident report and block the resource if safe

00:02:48.188 --> 00:02:56.026
use is not assured. Then document the repair and functional

00:02:56.026 --> 00:03:03.864
check. Only a successful check with a closing note permits

00:03:03.864 --> 00:03:09.350
release and makes the resource bookable again.

00:03:10.350 --> 00:03:18.944
Recurring appointments are suitable for repeating house-managed occupancy or blocked times.

00:03:18.944 --> 00:03:27.538
Choose the resource, weekday, time slot and validity period carefully. Review

00:03:27.538 --> 00:03:35.350
existing entries regularly so obsolete appointments do not block capacity.

00:03:36.350 --> 00:03:44.944
Analytics shows usage, utilization and operational patterns for your house. It

00:03:44.944 --> 00:03:53.538
supports capacity planning and maintenance decisions. Do not use these figures

00:03:53.538 --> 00:04:01.350
as a ranking or for public evaluation of individual residents.

00:04:02.350 --> 00:04:09.100
Security-sensitive actions require your current password and sometimes an

00:04:09.100 --> 00:04:15.850
exact confirmation phrase. Recheck the target account, house and

00:04:15.850 --> 00:04:22.600
impact before submitting. Never share your password or perform

00:04:22.600 --> 00:04:29.350
a critical action on request without verifying it yourself.

00:04:30.350 --> 00:04:37.273
As a house administrator, you manage apartments, accounts, resources and

00:04:37.273 --> 00:04:44.196
technical workflows for your assigned house. You do not create

00:04:44.196 --> 00:04:51.119
private bookings on behalf of residents. Other houses, global system

00:04:51.119 --> 00:04:57.350
settings and super administrator rights remain outside your role.
